Stakeholder Interests Documentation:

Stakeholder interests documentation identifies the expectations, needs, and level of influence of each stakeholder involved in CookSnap –
Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images. Understanding these interests helps in designing a system that satisfies user requirements and 
ensures successful project implementation.

Stakeholder Interests and Influence

• End Users (Home Cooks, Students, Working Professionals):
Interests: Quick recipe suggestions, accurate ingredient detection, reduced food wastage, ease of use
Influence: Medium – User feedback impacts system usability and acceptance

• System Developers / Project Team:
Interests: System accuracy, performance, maintainability, and successful project completion
Influence: High – Responsible for design, development, and implementation

• Project Instructor / Evaluator:
Interests: Correct requirement analysis, proper documentation, and application of software engineering principles
Influence: High – Approves requirements and evaluates project quality

• Recipe Data Providers / Content Sources:
Interests: Proper use, attribution, and representation of recipe data
Influence: Medium – Data quality affects recommendation accuracy

• Platform Administrators / Hosting Providers:
Interests: System availability, scalability, security, and reliability
Influence: Medium – Ensure stable system operation

• Future Maintainers or Researchers:
Interests: Clear documentation, modular design, and ease of system extension
Influence: Low to Medium – Indirect impact on long-term system evolution
